sentences: Dejan Orešković (born March 24, 1970), also known by his nickname Klo, is a Croatian record producer and guitarist.
In the following period, he played in various local bands, and in 1988, he became a member of the most popular local band Casablanca, at that time in a contract with Jugoton.
In 1994, he returned to Croatia and settled in Zagreb.
Invited by his longtime acquaintance Toni Lović, he became a member of band Hard Time where he played the bass guitar until 1997.
There, he performed on their ninth studio album Od neba do neba (2003).
Orešković left the Jagode band in 2005.
Since 2008, he has been a member of the rock band Zabranjeno Pušenje.
He performed on their last three studio albums; Muzej revolucije (2009), Radovi na cesti (2013), and Šok i nevjerica (2018).
